 stack that does not tie up cpu_resources with its 1 hour (3600,000)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="|_T!GZp(I#0Z-TLI`z}3"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="6w4~MnBHKcK$8X`#TLo/"><field name="TEXT">Also the 'if(false)' mini-stacks will be skipped by cpu, for further non-resource burdening</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="wL0E-DFr^_rL/*BAl,4y"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="@+Zz8M)hxB-JM.8ZD6dJ"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="O.IDl?mKWldVE)%G*CBy"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="i^{I=`Pd]uY;!z9,O=K("><field name="TEXT">Staff: Very Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="]680lDZO{n.f[||o]lX;"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="f:2[9j{i;%6=0^ivvg(w"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="xnRj1t.g#y(0/f7n-4hy"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="_B}W2s.MA+HBQ`W1CSu~"><field name="TEXT">Levels 1, 2, 2.1</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="XiHdH)svvid,jFcQPjC/"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="o5lX~8DH#/]coiosR3wC"><field name="TEXT">* Level 1: Hardcoded Static via Actual_Numbers for MotorPower%</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="-K4Y(mBmTnzE8iGgCJ}%"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="xdtaSxy/l=3c;3wv}G#l"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2: Softcoded Dynamic via Variables/Constants for MotorPower% </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="glDXO$!Y0k(p@EkYn}G%"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="{M=j]#njhsem.@Ovm,#r"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2.1 Add Controller_Joystick * Level 2.2 Add Gear 3 (90%?)</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="DRYm|qRXvW)lkMH*|[}n"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="t7CaRrWk0i6G^Q|`CsDS"><field name="TEXT">Basic Comment_Colors Usage:: Black: Very Big Picture, Blue: Big Picture, Green: Following Block_Code Moddable, Orange: Question/TODO, Magenta: Special Multi-Purpose </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="VSy+%B5NzAIrv6[v#j.b"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="nutOCIjwZ!,U`{!r#M!Y"><field name="TEXT">micro:bit Ver2 Warning during Download is Ignorable Yet Courteously Helpful</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="EJ~~!:Ex9RG^`avVe,:D"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="AmGtw:g27]~IGB1oE#i%"><field name="TEXT">'if_then' mini-stacks useful for modular 3-D code select/duplicate/move/delete</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="}%0?3UT(5%hkT9Xj(xcn"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="0d2FN}%6`WGAOzLEsHIf"><field name="TEXT">Light_Gray Functions non-editable (backend staff-use code only)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Dv[%$MAlH@`2mctu/wQk"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="R28#%0tyS-CkZoBJ3H+s"><field name="TEXT">For Group_CHannel_# (Bot_Id): Propose: 1-10 Staff Use, 11-99 Student Use</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="DH~KxXB`~3fS0cu`Dk4$"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="hz`:bBh:|]tyD?ia9W1a"><field name="TEXT">SW Reset: Long_Press Logo for 3 sec min</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="T8^@*/op^9j*xD~;y|-}"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="t,|IM/FTTTy:;RmV7~9i"><field name="TEXT">Built-in Diagnostic Test: Short_Press Logo for 1 sec max</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="`Op$gz8:)iVP.Q*JRu8="><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="#R*RYfY|{x[|@ro9rpJ4"><field name="TEXT">'Blocks' Window homes 'on start'_stack as top_left corner of editor_screen, until 'on start' is moved below, then next stack to right presides</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="EZ.zOWIMxTOOvNylIQGf"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="}d=oGMTo;W%TRZedv7aJ"><field name="TEXT">All These Levels are Intermediate Level Coding due to Networking Pairing Involved.  Basic Diagnostic Servo_Motors (Autonomoous) is Beginner Level.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="h?i=/1f)PO,OT=.SVF-g"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="v;t?wGHW!RDN]*Dp?GSr"><field name="TEXT">This Intermediate Level Network_Pairing has 1sec_Lag Response Time; The Other Advanced Level Network_Pairing has Real_Time Response Time.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="9vsy[)rVdu_8t1XI$]S{"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="0hcWsb8c0o8b=A)=^6Dl"><field name="TEXT">For Level 1, can keep 'Forward: set manual_servo_motors' Block functional, yet reset to 0 all other 'set manual_servo_motors' Blocks for Discovery Learning</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="QD!EUa74rh6%k0TKB#XZ"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="lzNcs?.B0ZLBP6]7FF,2"><field name="TEXT">If duplicate stacks exist, then the highest stack is active and others are non_active</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="controls_if" id="gRo!Dv5tj*`]e=LtN:IU"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="+m=*;pR:+ShnUcLg^h:^"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="$WE?X~;@qf^Q**I_(Io2"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="B_#Z]sWQ2)uvHtWZG}YN"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id=":~mL#k(7Qs@[DnNKms}6"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="8h|f`rK_Go]zWhjPj9+Q"><field name="TEXT">Upon open file, Editor zooms in on closest stack to right of original_origin from project_creation</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="j^ee?VrV+%?$lPb0vm`^"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="tlAMG2e!3o}mxa*AJN`M"><field name="TEXT">Semantic Naming prefers '_' vs. '-' since latter can be conufused with minus_sign</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="nwf=/oJ-%V8Ofssw7m6v"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="}:D7?C#5A)03a]t=q/sI"><field name="TEXT">'every 360000 ms' (1 hour) Stacks can be ignored, esp w/ 'if false' embedded</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="|qOEU[YzWVjaE8YGW)Y|"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="b1h+8JGMlvb-],X~GNE:"><field name="TEXT">Avoid using 'show leds' Block since will cause lag &amp; degrade real-time response</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="4|ZMTBf9fWPGiS^d+xk3"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="9z@66E*vnlf?;PFO[k.Q"><field name="TEXT">Seems like 'signficant' changes to JavaScript can activate 'format code', rearrange stacks to original position</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="oSTLOX3Vg3DN6mv@e;_A"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="0|`EdV,3HR,$}A;0-1{$"><field name="TEXT">Important 'system' variables are 1) _system_Hw_DeviceType__* (Hw=Hardware) and 2) _system_Sw_ModeState__* (Sw=Software)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="iQIhjVja.7J*UA7ruuq("><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="reukPp{5g;P@)O_:p_S{"><field name="TEXT">If Buttons C-F for Gears/Misc, Maybe 'Logo Up/Down' for 'Servo_Arm Up/Down'</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="!a)zhtL9iNu6`_bn5#zL"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="0L]J^f![u3Ch{.nI?Aoq"><field name="TEXT">'Rotatedisplay' could be used on Bot's Led_Screen, but causes light flickering on bottom row, so maybe avoid</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Tp.}q]}Cf;ggx#vB!zdk"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id=".s]9=Nq#j-egzsdpkCPE"><field name="TEXT">Reliable/Faster Response If Screen_Led_Graphics After Important Action Blocks Above</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="93/Jgw0.QHfnV9PDnAFd"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="1Mg/;DGf@RPuF4i~]Ry6"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="FLW((tb2.TQe5Q;x*oIH"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="NX6]9`v=$$4U[O=qe7sh"><field name="TEXT">Main upgrade from Lv1 to Lv2 is replacing cpu_laggy 'show leds' block with cpu_fast 'plox x _ y _' block, such as below: </field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="-C9rxl5]vBOLPkvL8nlm"><mutation elseif="4" else="1"></mutation><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="K.lZP:9H4Ukd1$U!8TOc"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></sh